"I'm freezing in here."

01:27:38.128 --> 01:27:40.005
The dishes were in the sink

01:27:40.130 --> 01:27:43.555
and the house was unkempt.

01:27:45.719 --> 01:27:48.689
I had the fear that everybody was dead

01:27:48.805 --> 01:27:50.807
and pretending to be alive.

01:27:54.019 --> 01:27:55.896
One time, my old man

01:27:56.021 --> 01:27:57.864
was punching my mother

01:27:57.981 --> 01:27:59.608
and I went up the stairs

01:27:59.733 --> 01:28:01.030
and I went in the room.

01:28:01.151 --> 01:28:04.155
And I had so much adrenaline,

01:28:04.321 --> 01:28:05.743
and I looked at him

01:28:05.864 --> 01:28:08.868
and I fucking put my eyes
right through him

01:28:08.992 --> 01:28:10.710
and I said, "if you hit her again,

01:28:10.827 --> 01:28:13.080
I am going to kill you."

01:28:13.205 --> 01:28:14.297
(GUNSHOT)

01:28:14.456 --> 01:28:15.799
(POLICE SIREN)

01:28:17.459 --> 01:28:21.009
POLICE OFFICER: Copy. All available
units responding to a shooting.

01:28:21.129 --> 01:28:22.881
REPORTER: The son of actor Marlon Brando

01:28:23.006 --> 01:28:24.929
facing murder charges this morning.

01:28:25.050 --> 01:28:30.022
32-year-old Christian Brando accused
of shooting his half-sister's boyfriend.

01:28:30.138 --> 01:28:32.641
REPORTER 2:
Ayoung man, Christian Brando.

01:28:32.766 --> 01:28:35.019
His half-sister, Cheyenne Brando.

01:28:35.143 --> 01:28:36.986
And her boyfriend.

01:28:37.103 --> 01:28:39.231
It was a triangle that proved fatal

01:28:39.439 --> 01:28:41.612
and brought tragedy to the home

01:28:41.733 --> 01:28:44.907
of one of the world's most famous stars.

01:28:45.028 --> 01:28:46.655
LAWYER: "I shot him, man."

01:28:46.822 --> 01:28:48.665
"But not on purpose."

01:28:48.824 --> 01:28:50.417
<i>"it was an accident."</i>

01:28:50.534 --> 01:28:52.252
REPORTER: The two men had quarreled

01:28:52.369 --> 01:28:54.463
over Drollet's treatment
of Cheyenne Brando.

01:28:54.579 --> 01:28:58.379
Mistreatment police say allegedly
included physical beating.

01:28:58.500 --> 01:29:01.800
LAWYER:
"Two guys with a loaded gun, wrestling."

01:29:02.420 --> 01:29:04.843
"it goes off and he's dead."

01:29:08.635 --> 01:29:10.888
I saw Dag laying there

01:29:11.847 --> 01:29:14.691
and I breathed into his mouth

01:29:14.808 --> 01:29:16.731
and I called 911.

01:29:18.186 --> 01:29:20.154
REPORTER: Asking leniency for his son,

01:29:20.272 --> 01:29:24.823
Brando said Christian's life had been
filled with struggle and unhappiness,

01:29:24.943 --> 01:29:27.867
traumatized by a bitter divorce.

01:29:27.988 --> 01:29:30.457
I think that
perhaps I failed as a father.

01:29:30.615 --> 01:29:33.710
And certainly there were things
that I could've done differently,

01:29:33.827 --> 01:29:35.500
had I known better at the time.

01:29:35.620 --> 01:29:37.463
I am at fault in this.

01:29:37.581 --> 01:29:41.336
And if I could trade places with Dag,
I would.

01:29:41.459 --> 01:29:45.305
The total sentence imposed
is ten years in the state prison.

01:29:46.590 --> 01:29:50.185
REPORTER: Cheyenne Brando is suffering
from mental and physical problems

01:29:50.385 --> 01:29:53.138
and cannot travel here
to testify about what she knows.

01:29:53.263 --> 01:29:55.561
Cheyenne is doing her best...

01:29:59.895 --> 01:30:02.648
Excuse me... sorry.

01:30:03.440 --> 01:30:06.535
REPORTER: Another personal tragedy
for actor Marlon Brando.

01:30:06.651 --> 01:30:09.074
His 25-year-old daughter Cheyenne

01:30:09.195 --> 01:30:11.573
has committed suicide at her home
in Tahiti.

01:30:11.698 --> 01:30:14.793
Cheyenne Brando reportedly
had made several suicide attempts

01:30:14.910 --> 01:30:17.083
before hanging herself yesterday.

01:30:18.830 --> 01:30:20.207
REPORTER 2: For Marlon Brando,

01:30:20.332 --> 01:30:24.087
Tahiti will never quite be
the same again.

01:30:39.184 --> 01:30:43.234
When in disgrace
with fortune and men's eyes,

01:30:43.355 --> 01:30:46.074
I all alone beweep my outcast state,

01:30:46.191 --> 01:30:47.818
and trouble deaf heaven

01:30:47.943 --> 01:30:50.287
with my bootless cries,

01:30:50.445 --> 01:30:53.790
and look upon myself and curse my fate.

01:31:04.292 --> 01:31:06.920
BRANDO: There are times
when you wake up in the morning

01:31:07.045 --> 01:31:10.675
and you turn over and feel,
"Shit! What a life."

01:31:13.593 --> 01:31:15.345
God, I can't figure it out.

01:31:15.512 --> 01:31:17.139
Why did it have to be this way?

01:31:19.599 --> 01:31:20.976
I've had a hard year.

01:31:22.727 --> 01:31:25.697
Maybe harder
than you could possibly imagine.

01:31:31.903 --> 01:31:35.953
<i>You try to be as strong as you can be,</i>

01:31:36.074 --> 01:31:39.954
but everybody reaches break point
sooner or later.

01:31:42.080 --> 01:31:45.584
Pain - I knew I had to deal with it.

01:31:47.002 --> 01:31:53.180
I've spent thousands upon thousands
of dollars on psychoanalysts

01:31:53.299 --> 01:31:56.894
and those guys do absolutely nothing

01:31:57.012 --> 01:32:01.017
but stick pliers and screwdrivers
in your brain.

01:32:03.226 --> 01:32:05.900
Life will have given me the truth

01:32:06.021 --> 01:32:08.194
and taken in exchange

01:32:08.314 --> 01:32:10.237
what's left of my youth.

01:32:12.068 --> 01:32:14.366
It took me a while to realize,

01:32:14.529 --> 01:32:16.827
you gotta be your own analyst.

01:32:18.825 --> 01:32:20.793
Unless we look inwards,

01:32:20.910 --> 01:32:24.960
we will not ever be able
to clearly see outwards.

01:32:26.791 --> 01:32:29.294
Nobody is born evil.

01:32:29.419 --> 01:32:33.469
Most people are simply
getting over bad emotional habits

01:32:33.631 --> 01:32:36.931
established in the first ten years
of their life.

01:32:40.055 --> 01:32:44.401
Christian was burdened
with emotional disorders

01:32:44.601 --> 01:32:47.400
and psychological disarray.

01:32:47.562 --> 01:32:50.065
The kind of trouble that I had in life.

01:32:53.068 --> 01:32:55.617
I never tried to be like my father,

01:32:55.737 --> 01:32:58.490
but one inadvertently takes on

01:32:58.656 --> 01:33:01.580
the characteristics of one's parents.

01:33:03.328 --> 01:33:05.251
When my father died,

01:33:05.413 --> 01:33:08.007
I imagined that he was slump-shouldered,

01:33:08.124 --> 01:33:11.503
walking to the edge of eternity.

01:33:11.711 --> 01:33:13.839
He looked back and said,

01:33:13.963 --> 01:33:15.886
"I did the best I could, kid."

01:33:17.717 --> 01:33:19.469
Finally I forgave my father,

01:33:19.636 --> 01:33:24.267
because I realized
that I was a sinner because of him.

01:33:24.390 --> 01:33:25.642
But he was a sinner,

01:33:25.767 --> 01:33:28.316
because his mother left him
when he was four.

01:33:28.436 --> 01:33:30.063
He didn't have a chance.

01:33:32.774 --> 01:33:35.744
And through introspection

01:33:35.860 --> 01:33:38.238
and the examination of my mind,

01:33:38.363 --> 01:33:40.491
I feel as though I'm coming closer

01:33:40.657 --> 01:33:42.534
to the common denominator

01:33:42.700 --> 01:33:44.748
of what it means to be human.

01:33:49.499 --> 01:33:52.673
Everybody is capable of hatred,

01:33:52.794 --> 01:33:55.217
everybody is capable of love.

01:33:55.380 --> 01:33:58.384
If we stretched ourselves
one way or another,

01:33:58.550 --> 01:34:00.052
we could become murderers

01:34:00.176 --> 01:34:02.099
or we could become saints.

01:34:03.555 --> 01:34:05.557
I've done a lot of meditation.

01:34:05.723 --> 01:34:09.023
The result is that
I have felt much calmer

01:34:09.144 --> 01:34:12.819
and I've had moments
of real tranquility.

01:34:14.149 --> 01:34:18.370
Don't you realize that you're thought of
as the greatest actor ever?

01:34:18.486 --> 01:34:20.705
Tim's the greatest actor ever.

01:34:20.822 --> 01:34:23.951
He pretends he loves me when he wants
something to eat. Get outta here.

01:34:25.368 --> 01:34:29.123
BRANDO: Many times
I remember being down in the dumps

01:34:29.247 --> 01:34:31.045
and then I saw a movie

01:34:31.166 --> 01:34:34.136
that took me away for a few hours

01:34:34.252 --> 01:34:36.755
and I was completely restored.

01:34:38.590 --> 01:34:40.809
And I realized, oddly enough,

01:34:40.925 --> 01:34:43.929
that actors make a contribution
to people's lives,

01:34:44.053 --> 01:34:47.102
giving us a gift that you can't buy.

01:34:48.016 --> 01:34:50.485
Something that they can imbue

01:34:50.685 --> 01:34:52.938
with power and beauty and magnificence.

01:34:53.062 --> 01:34:55.064
Something beyond themselves

01:34:55.190 --> 01:34:56.988
and we do need that.

01:34:58.568 --> 01:35:02.072
Acting is just making stuff up,

01:35:02.197 --> 01:35:03.699
but that's okay.

01:35:03.823 --> 01:35:05.621
Life is a rehearsal,

01:35:05.742 --> 01:35:07.335
life is an improvisation.

01:35:08.786 --> 01:35:12.256
I'm gonna have a special microphone
placed in my coffin,

01:35:12.373 --> 01:35:14.876
so that when I wake up in there,

01:35:15.001 --> 01:35:16.344
six feet under the ground,

01:35:16.461 --> 01:35:19.135
I'm gonna say, "Do it differently."

01:35:23.593 --> 01:35:27.063
Anthony. Come here, come here.

01:35:29.432 --> 01:35:31.184
BRANDO: The death scene.

01:35:31.309 --> 01:35:32.982
That's a tough scene to play.

01:35:34.896 --> 01:35:38.776
You have to make them believe
that you're dying.

01:35:38.900 --> 01:35:42.120
I would hope it would be
with one person.

01:35:42.237 --> 01:35:44.114
It would be something simple,

01:35:44.239 --> 01:35:46.617
like playing tiddlywinks

01:35:46.783 --> 01:35:50.128
or... I don't know, jackstraws.

01:35:51.246 --> 01:35:52.338
(MOANS)

01:35:54.332 --> 01:35:56.676
- (ANTHONY CRIES)
- CORLEONE: Oh, no! (LAUGHS)

01:35:58.086 --> 01:35:59.588
(CORLEONE LAUGHS)

01:36:01.381 --> 01:36:04.055
BRANDO: Try to think
of the most intimate moment

01:36:04.175 --> 01:36:06.177
that you've ever had in your life.

01:36:07.637 --> 01:36:09.639
Run down in there. Run in there.

01:36:11.099 --> 01:36:12.476
ANTHONY: Where are you?

01:36:12.976 --> 01:36:14.523
(LAUGHS)

01:36:16.479 --> 01:36:18.948
(COUGHS)

01:36:39.877 --> 01:36:43.632
BRANDO: Marlon. Listen to my voice.

01:36:44.674 --> 01:36:46.802
Just let go.

01:36:47.719 --> 01:36:49.517
Just letting go.

01:36:50.888 --> 01:36:52.390
Drift.

01:36:52.515 --> 01:36:55.439
Drift like a cloud in the sky.

01:36:57.603 --> 01:37:00.652
Drifting into that special state,

01:37:00.815 --> 01:37:02.158
the state of peace

01:37:02.275 --> 01:37:04.949
of the boy that you remember,

01:37:05.069 --> 01:37:07.163
watching the elm leaves come down.

01:37:13.202 --> 01:37:15.671
Don't hang on to thoughts,

01:37:15.830 --> 01:37:17.753
don't hang on to anything.

01:37:19.751 --> 01:37:22.049
They're old tapes,

01:37:22.170 --> 01:37:23.888
no longer usable,

01:37:24.047 --> 01:37:25.344
no longer useful.

01:37:26.924 --> 01:37:28.642
Chuck 'em.

01:37:28.760 --> 01:37:31.639
Put 'em aside. You don't need 'em.

01:37:33.431 --> 01:37:36.685
You're there, you have arrived.

01:37:39.562 --> 01:37:43.863
Your mind is becoming quieter
and quieter.

01:37:44.859 --> 01:37:48.033
Bliss is coming over you...

01:37:50.406 --> 01:37:51.783
Now.

01:37:53.201 --> 01:37:54.999
Until the next time.

01:37:59.165 --> 01:38:00.963
Sleep.

